messages.messageBody:
they didn't have patience for board games.God! I had rotten Parents! ! lol! Not really. :) they are gone now I miss them much.
----- Original Message -----
From: AimeeL73@...
To: Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Saturday, May 31, 2003 1:26 PM
Subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] 29 is still little, hee hee(was Re: 7 is still littl...


laurie97128@... writes:

<< Yea Aimee! What a delight you must be for you children! I never had that
as a child, my parents were not in good health. Laurie >>

Well, there are other ways to have fun, my grandma had various health
problems, but she taught me every board and card game I could ever want to know and
then some.

I never had that physical horsing around with my parents.... my mother is
entirely too proper to have static electricity in her hair, much less get her
twin set dirty....lol

~Aimee
